summary: Happy Birthday, Spider-man
title: Happy Birthday, Spider-man
body:
Soooooo, that dude’s turning 56 and I was gonna do an essay but it didn’t work out but I still wanted to post some something.

Thanks to Stan and Steve for creating such a great character with so many great things about him like the costume, the origin, the supporting cast, the relatability, the stories, the video games, the inspiration, the great creators who contributed to him like Bagley and Bendis and Stern and JRSR and JRJR and JMS and a million other things.

Love ya Spidey, here’s to another 56!

summary:
Couldn’t decide. Anyway, the concept behind this one is “what if Spider-Man got the anti-venom suit?”.

 I don’t read comics...
caption:
Couldn’t decide. Anyway, the concept behind this one is “what if Spider-Man got the anti-venom suit?”.

I don’t read comics directly (I grew up on the animations) but I do watch YT channels. From what I understand the Anti-Venom symbiote is the most practical.

It’s not fully sentient so it won’t take you over, it cures all impurities and even makes you deadly to touch for regular symbiotes and since it is derived from Venom it has spider powers.

Wearing it would probably purify Peter of his spider bite but since Venom and Anti-Venom have his powers anyway he wouldn’t really lose them.

summary: Samuel L Jackson and Cobie Smulders confirmed for ‘Spider-Man: Far From Home’
title: Samuel L Jackson and Cobie Smulders confirmed for ‘Spider-Man: Far From Home’
body:
Both the character were last seen in the post credits scene of the summer tentpole “Avengers: Infinity War”.

Entertainment News: Actors Samuel L Jackson and Cobie Smulders are all set to reprise their Marvel Cinematic Universe’s characters in “Spider-Man: Far From Home”.

According to Vulture, Jackson will return as Nick Fury in the sequel to 2017 blockbuster “Spider-Man: Homecoming”. Smulders will also reprise her role of S.H.I.E.L.D. agent Maria Hill.

Both the character were last seen in the post credits scene of the summer tentpole “Avengers: Infinity War”.

Spider Man: Far From Home Release Date

Jackson’s casting means that Nick Fury is confirmed to appear in at least two Marvel movies next year.

Apart from “Far From Home”, the actor will also appear opposite Brie Larson in “Captain Marvel”, which release on March 8, 2019.

Tom Holland will return as Peter Parker/Spider-Man in the sequel, the title of which was revealed by him in a social media gaffe.

Michael Keaton, Zendaya and Marisa Tomei will reprise their roles.

The film is also the Marvel debut of Jake Gyllenhaal, who is all set to play the antagonist, Mysterio in the….continue reading

News Source : BS
